TITLE: Tampermonkey @resource Directive for Preloading Script Resources
DESCRIPTION: The `@resource` directive preloads external resources, making them accessible via `GM_getResourceURL` and `GM_getResourceText` within the Tampermonkey script. It supports various URL types, including those with Subresource Integrity (SRI) hashes for security.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/documentation

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// @resource icon1       http://www.tampermonkey.net/favicon.ico
// @resource icon2       /images/icon.png
// @resource html        http://www.tampermonkey.net/index.html
// @resource xml         http://www.tampermonkey.net/crx/tampermonkey.xml
// @resource SRIsecured1 http://www.tampermonkey.net/favicon.ico#md5=123434...
// @resource SRIsecured2 http://www.tampermonkey.net/favicon.ico#md5=123434...;sha256=234234...
```

TITLE: Tampermonkey: Subresource Integrity (SRI) with @resource and @require
DESCRIPTION: Subresource Integrity (SRI) is a security feature that ensures external resources (like JavaScript libraries and CSS files) included via @require and @resource tags have not been tampered with. This is achieved by including cryptographic hashes (MD5, SHA-256, SHA-1, SHA-384, SHA-512) in the URL. Tampermonkey calculates the resource's hash and compares it; if they don't match, the resource is not loaded. Tampermonkey natively supports SHA-256 and MD5 hashes.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/documentation

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// @resource SRIsecured1 http://example.com/favicon1.ico#md5=ad34bb...
// @resource SRIsecured2 http://example.com/favicon2.ico#md5=ac3434...,sha256=23fd34...
// @require              https://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.1.min.js#md5=45eef...
// @require              https://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.2.min.js#md5-ac56d...,sha256-6e789...
// @require              https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js#sha256-/xUj+3OJU...ogEvDej/m4=
```

TITLE: Tampermonkey: Sync Scripts Across Browsers
DESCRIPTION: Describes the procedure to enable script synchronization in Tampermonkey using various services like Google Drive, Dropbox, WebDAV, and Browser Sync. It outlines the steps to configure sync and notes specific requirements and limitations for each service.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/faq

LANGUAGE: Plain Text
CODE:
```
1. Go to Tampermonkey's Dashboard and select the "Settings" tab.
2. Set the "Config Mode" to either "Beginner" or "Advanced".
3. Search for the "Script Sync" section.
4. Choose your preferred sync service (Google Drive, Dropbox, WebDAV, Browser Sync).
5. Enable "Script Sync" and press the "Save" button.

Sync Service Details:
- Google Drive: Requires a Google Account; stores data in a special app folder.
- Dropbox: Requires a Dropbox account; Tampermonkey will not run scripts at Dropbox related URLs.
- WebDAV: Can use any WebDAV server; may require credentials; Tampermonkey will not run scripts at the server's URLs.
- Browser Sync: Uses browser's internal service; limited data amount; requires a publicly accessible URL for scripts with @downloadURL.
```

TITLE: Fixing Tampermonkey Content Script Execution Order Bug in Chromium
DESCRIPTION: Addresses a Chromium bug causing Tampermonkey's content scripts to run in the wrong order, leading to delayed script execution. It provides a simple fix involving disabling and re-enabling the extension, and a more drastic solution of re-installing Tampermonkey if the initial fix fails.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/faq

LANGUAGE: Text
CODE:
```
This is caused by a bug in Chromium that causes Tampermonkey's content scripts to run in the wrong order.
Unfortunately the order matters and due to timing constraints it is not possible to wait longer for the other content script than already done.
This bug "only" happens when the extension is updated from a previous stable version lower than 4.18.
To fix the issue simply:

* Disable Tampermonkey extension
* Restart browser (make sure that all browser processes are gone, better restart the computer)
* Enable Tampermonkey extension
* Restart browser

Disabling the extension seems to cleanup things and the content scripts are executed in the right order again.

If it still doesn't work, then please

* export your settings and scripts (you can try importing them into the BETA version first to be on the safe side) and
* re-install Tampermonkey and
* import the backup again.
```

TITLE: Tampermonkey API: GM_addElement (Experimental)
DESCRIPTION: The GM_addElement function allows Tampermonkey scripts to dynamically add new HTML elements to the page, which can be useful for bypassing Content Security Policies (CSPs) that restrict script or image tags. It creates an HTML element specified by 'tag_name', applies all given 'attributes', and returns the injected element. If a 'parent_node' is provided, the element is attached to it; otherwise, it's attached to the document head or body. This feature is experimental and its API may change.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/documentation

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
GM_addElement(tag_name: string, attributes: object): HTMLElement
GM_addElement(parent_node: Node, tag_name: string, attributes: object): HTMLElement
  tag_name: The HTML tag name (e.g., 'script', 'img', 'style').
  attributes: An object containing attributes to apply to the new element.
  parent_node: (Optional) The DOM node to which the new element will be appended. Defaults to document head or body.
  Returns: The newly created and injected HTML element.
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
GM_addElement('script', {
  textContent: 'window.foo = "bar";'
});

GM_addElement('script', {
  src: 'https://example.com/script.js',
  type: 'text/javascript'
});

GM_addElement(document.getElementsByTagName('div')[0], 'img', {
  src: 'https://example.com/image.png'
});

GM_addElement(shadowDOM, 'style', {
  textContent: 'div { color: black; };'
});
```

TITLE: Enabling User Script Execution Permissions for Tampermonkey 5.3+ in Chrome/Edge
DESCRIPTION: Details the necessary permissions for Tampermonkey version 5.3+ in Chrome-based browsers to execute userscripts. SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/faq

LANGUAGE: Text
CODE:
```
For users of the Tampermonkey extension (version 5.3+) in a Chrome-based browser, enabling either the **"Allow User Scripts" toggle** (available in Chrome 138+ via extension settings) or **Developer Mode** is required.

### Why is permission to execute userscripts necessary?

An additional permission is required due to the two-step authorization process for userscripts: the `userScripts` permission and either the toggle or Developer Mode.
The `userScripts` permission alone doesn't trigger a user warning upon installation, reflecting Google's intent to ensure informed decisions when running extensions that use Userscripts.

### Steps to enable

To enable these settings:

#### In desktop Chrome/Edge 138+:

1. Open extension settings by right-clicking the Tampermonkey icon **(1)** and selecting "Manage Extension" **(2)**.
2. Locate and enable the **"Allow User Scripts" toggle**.

#### In desktop Chrome/Edge:

1. Navigate to `chrome://extensions` or `edge://extensions` in a new tab.
2. Enable **Developer Mode** by clicking the toggle at the top right.

#### In Microsoft Edge Android:

1. Follow the step-by-step sequence in the image below to enable Developer Mode.

This action enables the use of the `userScripts` API through Tampermonkey.
```

TITLE: Example: Displaying a Tampermonkey Notification with Click Handler

```
  }
});
```

TITLE: GM_download: Download a file from a URL
DESCRIPTION: The `GM_download` function enables userscripts to download files from a specified URL to the user's local machine. It supports various options for file naming, HTTP headers, save location prompts, and conflict resolution. Callbacks are provided for success, error, progress, and timeout events. The function returns an object with an `abort` method to cancel the download. The promise-based `GM.download` returns a promise that resolves to download details and also has an `abort` function.

SOURCE: https://www.tampermonkey.net/documentation.php/documentation

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
GM_download(details), GM_download(url, name)

Description: Allows userscripts to download a file from a specified URL and save it to the user's local machine.

Parameters:
  details (object):
    url: string | Blob | File - The URL of the file to download or a Blob/File object (v5.4.6226+).
    name: string - The name to use for the downloaded file (e.g., ".txt" or ".pdf"). File extension must be whitelisted.
    headers: object - HTTP headers to include in the download request (see GM_xmlhttpRequest).
    saveAs: boolean - Whether to prompt the user to choose a different location (browser API mode only).
    conflictAction: string - Action when a file with this name already exists ('uniquify', 'overwrite', 'prompt') (browser API mode only).
    onload: function - Callback when the download has completed successfully.
    onerror: function - Callback if the download fails or is cancelled.
    onprogress: function - Callback if this download made some progress.
    ontimeout: function - Callback if this download failed due to a timeout.

onerror callback (download argument attributes):
  error: string - Error reason:
    - not_enabled: download feature isn't enabled by the user.
    - not_whitelisted: requested file extension is not whitelisted.
    - not_permitted: user enabled download feature, but did not give 'downloads' permission.
    - not_supported: download feature isn't supported by the browser/version.
    - not_succeeded: download wasn't started or failed.
  details: string - Detail about that error.

Returns (object):
  abort: function - A function which can be called to cancel this download.

GM.download (Promise-based version):
  Returns a Promise that resolves to the download details and also has an 'abort' function.

GM_info.downloadMode: string - Property indicating the current download mode ('native', 'disabled', 'browser').
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
GM_download("http://example.com/file.txt", "file.txt");

const download = GM_download({
    url: "http://example.com/file.txt",
    name: "file.txt",
    saveAs: true
});

// cancel download after 5 seconds
window.setTimeout(() => download.abort(), 5000);
```

### 1. 使用 `@require` 指令（推荐方式）

```diff
+             console.error('❌ 外部资源加载失败: startAPIMonitor 函数不可用');
+             
+             // 备用方案：动态加载
+             loadResourceDynamically();
+         }
+     }
+     
+     // 备用方案：动态加载外部资源
+     function loadResourceDynamically() {
+         console.log('🔄 尝试动态加载外部资源...');
+         
+         const script = document.createElement('script');
+         script.src = 'https://your-cdn.com/api-monitor-standalone.js';
+         script.type = 'text/javascript';
+         
+         script.onload = function() {
+             console.log('✅ 动态加载成功');
+             // 延迟检查，确保脚本执行完成
+             setTimeout(checkResourceLoaded, 100);
+         };
+         
+         script.onerror = function() {
+             console.error('❌ 动态加载失败: 网络错误或资源不存在');
+             
+             // 尝试本地备用方案
+             loadLocalBackup();
+         };
+         
+         document.head.appendChild(script);
+     }
+     
+     // 本地备用方案
+     function loadLocalBackup() {
+         console.log('🔄 尝试加载本地备用方案...');
+         
+         // 这里可以嵌入你的监控器代码作为备用
+         // 或者尝试其他CDN源
+         const backupScript = document.createElement('script');
+         backupScript.src = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/your-username/your-repo@main/api-monitor-standalone.js';
+         backupScript.type = 'text/javascript';
+         
+         backupScript.onload = function() {
+             console.log('✅ 备用方案加载成功');
+             setTimeout(checkResourceLoaded, 100);
+         };
+         
+         backupScript.onerror = function() {
+             console.error('❌ 所有加载方案都失败了');
+             alert('API监控器加载失败，请检查网络连接或联系开发者');
+         };
+         
+         document.head.appendChild(backupScript);
+     }
+     
+     // 等待页面加载完成后检查资源
+     if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
+         document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', checkResourceLoaded);
+     } else {
+         // 页面已经加载完成，直接检查
+         setTimeout(checkResourceLoaded, 100);
+     }
      
  })(); 
```

+ # 油猴脚本引入外部资源最佳实践
+ 
+ ## 概述
+ 
+ 本文档介绍在Tampermonkey油猴脚本中引入第三方JavaScript资源包的最佳实践，包括多种加载方式、错误处理、备用方案等。
+ 
+ ## 支持的加载方式
+ 
+ ### 1. @require 指令（推荐）
+ 
+ **优点：**
+ - 最安全的方式
+ - 支持子资源完整性验证（SRI）
+ - 在脚本执行前加载
+ - 自动处理依赖关系
+ 
+ **用法：**
+ ```javascript
+ // ==UserScript==
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/api-monitor-standalone.js
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/api-monitor-standalone.js#sha256=your-hash-here
+ // ==/UserScript==
+ ```
+ 
+ **SRI哈希验证：**
+ ```javascript
+ // 支持多种哈希算法
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/script.js#md5=123456...
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/script.js#sha256=abcdef...
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/script.js#md5=123456...,sha256=abcdef...
+ ```
+ 
+ ### 2. @resource 指令
+ 
+ **优点：**
+ - 预加载资源
+ - 可通过GM_getResourceText获取内容
+ - 支持SRI验证
+ 
+ **用法：**
+ ```javascript
+ // ==UserScript==
+ // @resource     MONITOR_SCRIPT https://your-cdn.com/api-monitor-standalone.js
+ // ==/UserScript==
+ 
+ // 在脚本中使用

+ ```
+ 
+ ### 3. GM_addElement（推荐用于动态加载）
+ 
+ **优点：**
+ - 绕过CSP限制
+ - 支持动态加载
+ - 更好的错误处理
+ 
+ **用法：**

+ // 需要 @grant GM_addElement
+ const script = GM_addElement('script', {
+     src: 'https://your-cdn.com/api-monitor-standalone.js',
+     type: 'text/javascript'

+

+ - 支持多个备用源
+ 
+ **用法：**

+ script.onload = () => console.log('加载成功');
+ script.onerror = () => console.log('加载失败');
+ document.head.appendChild(script);
+ ```
+ 
+ ## 错误处理和备用方案
+ 
+ ### 1. 多重加载策略
+ 
+ ```javascript
+ class ResourceLoader {
+     async load() {
+         const loadMethods = [
+             () => this.loadViaRequire(),
+             () => this.loadViaResource(),
+             () => this.loadViaGMAddElement(),
+             () => this.loadDynamically(primaryCDN)
+         ];
+         
+         for (const method of loadMethods) {
+             try {
+                 await method();
+                 return true;
+             } catch (error) {
+                 console.warn(`加载方法失败: ${error.message}`);
+             }
+         }
+         
+         return await this.loadBackupCDNs();
+     }
+ }
+ ```
+ 
+ ### 2. 备用CDN源
+ 
+ ```javascript

+     'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/your-username/your-repo@main/script.js',
+     'https://unpkg.com/your-package@latest/script.js',
+     'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-username/your-repo/main/script.js'
+ ];
+ ```
+ 
+ ### 3. 超时和重试机制
+ 
+ ```javascript
+ const retryConfig = {
+     maxRetries: 3,
+     retryDelay: 1000,
+     timeout: 10000
+ };
+ ```
+ 
+ ## 最佳实践
+ 
+ ### 1. 权限配置
+ 
+ ```javascript
+ // ==UserScript==
+ // @grant        GM_xmlhttpRequest
+ // @grant        GM_addElement
+ // @grant        GM_getResourceText
+ // @grant        GM_log
+ // @connect      your-cdn.com
+ // @connect      cdn.jsdelivr.net
+ // @connect      unpkg.com
+ // ==/UserScript==
+ ```
+ 
+ ### 2. 资源完整性验证
+ 
+ ```javascript
+ // 使用SRI哈希确保资源完整性
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/script.js#sha256=your-hash-here
+ ```
+ 
+ ### 3. 错误检测和报告
+

+ function checkResourceLoaded() {
+     if (typeof window.startAPIMonitor === 'function') {
+         console.log('✅ 外部资源加载成功');
+         return true;
+     } else {
+         console.error('❌ 外部资源加载失败');

+         top: 10px;

+     `;

+         <strong>脚本加载错误</strong><br>
+         ${message}<br>
+         <small>请刷新页面重试</small>
+     `;
+     document.body.appendChild(errorDiv);
+ }
+ ```
+ 
+ ## 示例文件说明
+ 
+ ### simple-example.js
+ 基础版本的油猴脚本，使用简单的动态加载方式。
+ 
+ ### simple-example-advanced.js
+ 高级版本的油猴脚本，包含：
+ - 多种加载方式
+ - 完整的错误处理
+ - 备用CDN支持
+ - 用户友好的错误提示
+ - 详细的日志记录
+ 
+ ## 常见问题
+ 
+ ### Q: 为什么@require指令加载失败？
+ A: 可能的原因：
+ - 网络连接问题
+ - CDN服务不可用
+ - 资源URL错误
+ - CSP限制
+ 
+ ### Q: 如何处理CSP限制？
+ A: 使用GM_addElement或@resource指令，这些方式可以绕过CSP限制。
+ 
+ ### Q: 如何确保资源完整性？
+ A: 使用SRI哈希验证：
+ ```javascript
+ // @require      https://your-cdn.com/script.js#sha256=your-hash-here
+ ```
+ 
+ ### Q: 如何调试加载问题？
+ A: 使用浏览器开发者工具：
+ - 检查Network标签页
+ - 查看Console错误信息
+ - 使用GM_log记录详细日志
+ 
+ ## 安全注意事项
+ 
+ 1. **使用HTTPS**: 确保所有外部资源都通过HTTPS加载
+ 2. **SRI验证**: 使用子资源完整性验证防止资源被篡改
+ 3. **权限最小化**: 只请求必要的权限
+ 4. **错误处理**: 妥善处理加载失败的情况
+ 5. **备用方案**: 提供多个备用CDN源
+ 
+ ## 性能优化
+ 
+ 1. **缓存策略**: 利用浏览器缓存减少重复下载
+ 2. **异步加载**: 使用异步加载避免阻塞页面
+ 3. **按需加载**: 只在需要时加载资源
+ 4. **压缩资源**: 使用压缩版本的JavaScript文件
+ 
+ ## 总结
+ 
+ 推荐的使用顺序：
+ 1. 优先使用@require指令（最安全）
+ 2. 备用@resource指令
+ 3. 动态加载使用GM_addElement
+ 4. 最后使用传统动态加载
+ 
+ 确保提供完整的错误处理和用户友好的提示信息。

我找到了问题！在第161行，有一个语法错误。让我查看更具体的代码：


---

Read file: api-monitor-standalone.js

---

找到问题了！在第161行，有一个语法错误。问题是在箭头函数后面错误地添加了 `.bind(this)`。箭头函数已经自动绑定了 `this`，所以不需要再调用 `.bind(this)`。

让我修复这个问题：


---

<details><summary>Edit file: api-monitor-standalone.js</summary>

undefined

**Chunk 1**
Lines added: 1, lines removed: 1

```diff
@@ -159,5 +159,5 @@
                                  this.log('❌ 处理XHR响应出错:', e);
                              }
-                         }.bind(this));
+                         });
                      }
                      
```

_**Assistant**_

你的问题总结如下：

- 你发现**主资源加载失败**，但**备用CDN加载成功**，最终脚本能正常运行。
- 你想知道：为什么主资源会失败，而备用CDN能成功？出现这种情况的原因是什么？

---

## 1. 你的加载流程回顾

你的 `simple-example.js` 采用了如下加载流程：

1. **优先用主资源（GitHub Raw）加载**  
   `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jiangxiaoyu66/scritpts_cat_sdks/refs/heads/main/api-monitor-standalone.js`
2. **主资源失败后，尝试传统 script 标签加载主资源**
3. **主资源都失败后，尝试备用CDN（jsDelivr）加载**  
   `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/jiangxiaoyu66/scritpts_cat_sdks@main/api-monitor-standalone.js`
4. **备用CDN成功，脚本正常运行**

---

## 2. 为什么主资源会失败？

### 常见原因如下：

#### 1. **GitHub Raw 资源跨域（CORS）限制**
- **Tampermonkey** 虽然可以通过 `@connect` 允许跨域，但有些浏览器/环境对 `raw.githubusercontent.com` 的 script 资源有更严格的 CSP（内容安全策略）或 CORS 限制。
- **表现**：`<script src="...">` 方式加载时，浏览器会拦截，导致 `onerror` 触发，加载失败。

#### 2. **网络问题**
- 你的网络环境对 GitHub 访问不稳定，或者被墙，导致资源无法下载。

#### 3. **GitHub Raw 资源响应头问题**
- 有时 GitHub Raw 返回的 `Content-Type` 不是 `application/javascript`，而是 `text/plain`，部分浏览器会拒绝执行。

#### 4. **Tampermonkey/浏览器安全策略**
- 某些浏览器或 Tampermonkey 版本对外部脚本的加载有额外限制，尤其是非 HTTPS 或非白名单域名。

---

## 3. 为什么备用CDN（jsDelivr）能成功？

- **jsDelivr** 是专门为静态资源分发设计的 CDN，响应头、CORS、内容类型都做了优化，兼容性好。
- 速度快，国内外访问都比较稳定。
- 浏览器和 Tampermonkey 对 jsDelivr 的资源一般不会有额外限制。

---

## 4. 你可以怎么做？

- **主资源失败是正常现象**，尤其是用 GitHub Raw 作为 script 资源时。
- **备用CDN方案是最佳实践**，保证了高可用性。
- 如果你想让主资源也能成功，可以考虑：
  - 检查本地网络环境，确保能访问 `raw.githubusercontent.com`
  - 检查 Tampermonkey 的 `@connect` 是否包含了 `raw.githubusercontent.com`
  - 但**最推荐的做法**还是直接用 jsDelivr 这类 CDN 作为主资源，GitHub Raw 作为备用。

---

## 5. 结论

- **主资源失败**多半是因为 CORS、内容类型、网络等问题，不是你代码的问题。
- **备用CDN成功**说明你的降级方案是有效的，脚本能正常运行。
- 你可以放心使用 jsDelivr 作为主资源，GitHub Raw 作为备用，或者只用 jsDelivr。

```
✅ [API Monitor ...] 备用CDN加载成功
```

这说明你的降级机制工作正常，**最终能用就没问题**！

已为你重写脚本，采用**官方推荐的 `@require` 写法**，并且只用 jsDelivr CDN，不再做任何动态加载和降级处理，代码更简洁、稳定。

### 主要变更说明

1. **只用 jsDelivr CDN**  
   ```js
   // @require      https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/jiangxiaoyu66/scritpts_cat_sdks@main/api-monitor-standalone.js
   ```
2. **去除所有动态加载、降级、备用URL逻辑**  
   只保留核心启动和日志，结构更清晰。
3. **保留原有的监控配置和事件监听**  
   只要 `startAPIMonitor` 可用就直接启动。

---

### 现在的用法

只需保证 `@require` 行指向 jsDelivr CDN，Tampermonkey 会自动帮你加载依赖。你无需再手动写任何 script 标签或降级逻辑。

---

### 你可以直接复制如下头部到你的 userscript：

```js
// ==UserScript==
// @name         1688接口监控器 - 超简单版本
// @namespace    http://tampermonkey.net/
// @version      1.0.0
// @description  监控1688接口请求
// @author       Your name
// @match        *://air.1688.com/*
// @match        *://*.air.1688.com/*
// @require      https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/jiangxiaoyu66/scritpts_cat_sdks@main/api-monitor-standalone.js
// @grant        GM_log
// @run-at       document-start
// ==/UserScript==
```

后面只需保留启动逻辑即可。
